main event: A radar observation of an unidentified target near Laredo, Texas on October 11, 1958, was recorded as possibly being a meteor.
interesting points: The radar tracked two objects observed for approximately 28 seconds,The object was seen in multiple radar beams, indicating a sudden appearance,The range of the object placed it near the White Sands Proving Grounds,Conclusions pointed towards possible meteors due to speed and signal characteristics,No other radar targets were observed during the time frame of interest.
